The paper proposes a new type of neural network, specifically an enhancement of traditional Autoencoders, which is designed to learn a low dimensional representation of data enriched with a desired structure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as these are the most relevant areas for research on neural networks and image processing. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of weak supervision to form a structured latent space, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of the structured latent space for classification and morphing between classes, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions experiments on benchmark image datasets and a dataset of 3D human shapes, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category.
